Develop a Company Website with Wix is a self-hosted course project by Coursera. This course discusses and learns how to create a website to build a company. One of the highlights of this course is the faster creation of websites using a web builder tool called WIX without the need to program the web from scratch. BINTANG 5 ***

the course is created by the Coursera project network and takes about 2 hours to complete. In this project, using WIX as a platform for working on this project, there are three structures: an overview, an integrated project consisting of 6 tasks, and one quiz consisting of 10 questions. This project creates a website for a company or shop that we will build using an example of a cake shop. In this project, I learned how to create an account and choose a template for a website, make changes to media, text and design sections, manage menus and blogs, manage events, and manage menus that will appear on the website. This course helped me create a shop website without having to do any coding. Coursera provides a cloud workspace to help me while working on this course, located next to the video tutorial. However, the cloud workspace is quite heavy to run, so when doing this course, I chose not to use the cloud workspace, and I used my browser, which is connected to the WIX website. As long as I am working on this course, there are no obstacles that interfere with the work of this course, including the delivery of material using English because the video tutorial has provided subtitles by the Coursera. The delivery is clear enough to listen to.
